1.Cut
    --> Cut is a command line utility that allows you to cut parts of lines from specified files or piped data and print the result to 
standard output.it can be used to cut parts of a line by delimiter,byte position,and character

          1) Cut filename               ==      Does not work

          2) cut --version              ==      check version

          3) cut -c1 filename           ==      list one character

          4) cut -c1,2,4                ==      pick and choose character

          5) cut -c1-3 filename         ==      list range of characters

          6) cut -c1-3,6-8 filename     ==      list specific range of characters

          7) cut -b1-3 filename         ==      list by byte size

          8) cut -d:  or -d, or -d? -f 6 /etc/passwd   ==      list first 6th column separated by:  NOTE: delimiter only works on fileds not on characters

          9) cut -d: -f 6-7 /etc/passwd ==      list first 6 and 7th column separated by:

          10) ls -l | cut -c2-4         ==      only print user permisssions of filess or directory

