4.sort/uniq

  --> What are sort and uniq commands ?
       -> sort command sorts in alphabetical order
       -> uniq command filters out the repeated or duplicates lines

    1) sort --version OR sort --help              ==  check version or help
    2) sort filename                              ==  sorts files in alphabetical order
    3) sort -r filename                           ==  sort in reverse alphabetical order
    4) sort -k2 filename                          ==  sort by field number
    
    5) uniq file                                  == removes duplicates
    6) sort file | uniq                           == always sort first before using uniq
    7) sort file | uniq -c                        == sorts first and then uniq later gives list count
    8) sort file | uniq -d                        == only shows repeated lines

