5.wc[word count]
     
      --> What is wc command ?
         -> The command reads either standard input or a list of files and generates newline count,word count,and byte count.

         1) wc --version OR wc --help           == check version or help
         2) wc filename                         == check file line count,word count and byte count
         3) wc -l filename                      == get the number of lines in a file
         4) wc -w filename                      == get the number of words in a file
         5) wc -c filename                      == get the number of bytes in a file
         6) ls -l | wc -l                       == gives the number of files that are exitsed
         7) ls -l | grep drw | wc -l            == gives the number of directories that are existed
